.TH "TRACEE\-STORES" "1" "2025/12" "" "Tracee Stores Flag Manual"
.SS NAME
tracee \f[B]\-\-stores\f[R] \- Configure data stores for DNS cache and
process tree
.SS SYNOPSIS
tracee \f[B]\-\-stores\f[R]
[dns.enabled|dns.max\-entries=\f[I]size\f[R]|process.enabled|process.max\-processes=\f[I]size\f[R]|process.max\-threads=\f[I]size\f[R]|process.source=\f[I]source\f[R]|process.use\-procfs]
[\f[B]\-\-stores\f[R] \&...]
.SS DESCRIPTION
The \f[B]\-\-stores\f[R] flag allows you to configure data stores for
DNS cache and process tree functionality.
.SS DNS Store Options
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]dns.enabled\f[R]: Enable the DNS cache store.
When enabled, Tracee will cache DNS query information for enrichment of
network events.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]dns.max\-entries\f[R]=\f[I]size\f[R]: Set the maximum number of DNS
query trees to cache.
Default is 5000.
Further queries may be cached regardless once the limit is reached.
.SS Process Store Options
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]process.enabled\f[R]: Enable the process tree store.
When enabled, Tracee will maintain a tree of processes and threads for
enrichment of events.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]process.max\-processes\f[R]=\f[I]size\f[R]: Set the maximum number
of processes to cache in the process tree.
Default is 10928.
This is an LRU cache that will evict least recently accessed entries
when full.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]process.max\-threads\f[R]=\f[I]size\f[R]: Set the maximum number of
threads to cache in the process tree.
Default is 21856.
This is an LRU cache that will evict least recently accessed entries
when full.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]process.source\f[R]=\f[I]source\f[R]: Set the source for process
tree enrichment.
Valid values are:
.RS 2
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]none\f[R]: Process tree source is disabled (default).
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]events\f[R]: Process tree is built from events.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]signals\f[R]: Process tree is built from signals.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]both\f[R]: Process tree is built from both events and signals.
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]process.use\-procfs\f[R]: Enable procfs initialization and
querying.
When enabled, Tracee will:
.RS 2
.IP \[bu] 2
Scan procfs during initialization to fill all existing processes and
threads.
.IP \[bu] 2
Query specific processes at runtime in case of missing information
caused by missing events.
.PP
Note: The procfs query might increase the feature toll on CPU and
memory.
The runtime query might have a snowball effect on lost events, as it
will reduce the system resources in the processes of filling missing
information.
.RE
